Function declarations are hoisted always.

console.log(red(1,2));

function red(a,b)
{
    return a + b;
}




_______________________________________________

var red;
console.log(red);

we get undefined as we have not defined any value

_____________________________________________


console.log(red);

var red =56;//we get undefined error as the 

________________________________________________


console.log(red);
let red =56;

let is not defined error as let declarations are not hoisted
